cs.SE, cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.NE, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on performance modeling of adaptable software systems. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for performance modeling. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are possible categories as adaptable software systems often run in distributed or parallel environments and may use neural networks or evolutionary algorithms for self-adaptation. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may discuss the implementation of performance modeling algorithms in programming languages.
